52.1	Derek_Walcott	Derek Walcott	Derek Alton Walcott, OBE OCC (born 23 January 1930) is a Saint Lucian poet, playwright, writer and visual artist who was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1992; in 2001 he received the T. S. Eliot Prize for his book of poetry, White Egrets. His works include the Homeric epic poem, Omeros (1990). Robert Graves wrote that Walcott "handles English with a closer understanding of its inner magic than most, if not any, of his contemporaries‚Äù.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Derek_Walcott.jpg/220px-Derek_Walcott.jpg
